criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Diagnosis of ischemical brain injury or intracerebral hemorrhage by MRI or computed
             tomography at least 6 months before the onset of the study;

          -  Ability to walk in the treadmill at >0.3 km/h for 3 minutes handrail support;

          -  Be able to give informed consent and be motivated to participate in 3- month intensive
             physical fitness training.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Mini Mental State Examination <20;

          -  Unstable angina pectoris;

          -  Unstable cardiac conditions;

          -  Complex ventricular arrhythmia;

          -  Resting systolic blood pressure >200 mm/Hg - Resting diastolic blood pressure >100
             mm/Hg;

          -  Aphasia (unable to follow two commands);

          -  Other medical conditions precluding participation in aerobic exercise.
